00:19:41,813 --> 00:19:45,751
someone who went missing
in the prime of her life. 

245
00:19:47,584 --> 00:19:49,000
Batskelien! 

246
00:19:49,250 --> 00:19:52,250
My identical twin sister! HEYDRICH LAUGHS 

247
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:54,334
Did you find her? M-hm. 

248
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:59,834
Really?!
I've been paying a detective for years... 

249
00:20:00,042 --> 00:20:02,792
90 percent of my salary to find her! 

250
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,417
I know that, because that detective
is now her boyfriend... 

251
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:08,083
and they travel all over the world... 

252
00:20:08,334 --> 00:20:13,334
looking for exclusive full moon parties. 

253
00:20:13,584 --> 00:20:17,584
And they also have a very nice blog,
here look. 

254
00:20:17,834 --> 00:20:22,250
Because when I told her there was also
an exclusive full moon party here... 

255
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:26,167
she immediately flew over first class. 

256
00:20:26,417 --> 00:20:28,292
Jaha! 

257
00:20:31,083 --> 00:20:32,542
Great. 

258
00:20:40,584 --> 00:20:42,000
That... 

259
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,834
That is my holiday. 

260
00:20:45,042 --> 00:20:47,292
Vacation.
Say... 

261
00:20:47,584 --> 00:20:51,500
Your little sister is in the cupboard. 

262
00:21:51,751 --> 00:20:53,167
Cupboard open! 

263
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:09,584
Batskelien! No! 

264
00:21:09,834 --> 00:21:11,250
No! 

265
00:21:14,999 --> 00:21:16,751
No! 

266
00:21:19,209 --> 00:21:20,667
Batskelien! 

267
00:21:20,918 --> 00:21:23,250
What did you do to her? 

268
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:26,834
Now really, boys! 

269
00:21:30,209 --> 00:21:31,667
Why?! 

270
00:21:32,834 --> 00:21:35,042
Yes... Hello, eh... 

271
00:21:35,334 --> 00:21:39,083
Yes, eh... You had locked us in here
with the light off. 

272
00:21:40,709 --> 00:21:43,918
I didn't lock you in at all
with the light off! 

273
00:21:44,083 --> 00:21:47,292
Light on! Door open! 

274
00:21:50,834 --> 00:21:53,834
Yes, but we didn't know that. 

275
00:21:54,083 --> 00:21:56,000
And you opened that cupboard yourself. 

276
00:21:57,083 --> 00:21:59,709
Yes, Barteljaap, you opened the cupboard. 

277
00:21:59,999 --> 00:22:02,500
We thought we had ended up in
a horror show. 

278
00:22:02,751 --> 00:22:04,751
There's also a camera and everything. 

279
00:22:04,999 --> 00:22:07,500
I use that to film my lessons... 

280
00:22:07,751 --> 00:22:10,459
to find points for improvement
in myself. 

281
00:22:10,709 --> 00:22:12,918
If you had paid more money
to that detective... 

282
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:15,751
she would have had credit.
Then we could have called for help. 

283
00:21:59,999 --> 00:22:19,959
I understand it looks very strange like this,
but she looked very dead... 

284
00:22:20,167 --> 00:22:22,042
and then she attacked me and started
strangling me. 

285
00:22:22,292 --> 00:22:25,751
Oops! That might be my mistake. 

286
00:22:25,999 --> 00:22:29,116
I threw the schnapps and the nice
party things 

287
00:22:29,140 --> 00:22:31,459
in the cupboard with the girl. 

288
00:22:31,709 --> 00:22:37,709
But your sister also has a very bad
reaction to drink, you know! 

289
00:22:37,959 --> 00:22:42,042
There was also a corpse smell and everything.
Those were my little farts. 

290
00:22:42,292 --> 00:22:46,417
I am very insecure about my bowel movements.
Annoying. 

291
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:48,761
Anyway, luckily you had an ashtray 

292
00:22:48,785 --> 00:22:52,209
I could hit her with, because otherwise it
would have ended badly. 

293
00:22:52,459 --> 00:22:53,918
Ashtray? 

294
00:22:58,083 --> 00:23:01,417
No! No! Papa and mama! 

295
00:23:04,042 --> 00:23:05,834
HE CRIES 

296
00:23:08,584 --> 00:23:11,751
My whole family is lying here! 

297
00:23:14,959 --> 00:23:19,417
I love it when a plan works. 

298
00:23:19,709 --> 00:23:22,334
Sorry, what did you say? Nothing. 

299
00:23:30,584 --> 00:23:34,918
Sorry Barteljaap.
It was just an unfortunate misunderstanding. 

300
00:23:35,083 --> 00:23:37,709
Yes, can happen. 

301
00:23:42,083 --> 00:23:43,542
It's fine. 

302
00:23:43,834 --> 00:23:46,762
For too long I have let myself be
walked over 

303
00:23:46,786 --> 00:23:50,125
and let myself be used by everything
and everyone! 

304
00:23:50,375 --> 00:23:52,375
That is going to change from now on. 

305
00:23:52,626 --> 00:23:55,959
I may have lost my
identical twin sister... 

306
00:23:56,167 --> 00:23:58,167
but I am going to find myself! 

307
00:23:58,417 --> 00:23:59,876
I find it sad. 

308
00:24:00,083 --> 00:24:02,083
Barteljaap all alone. 

309
00:24:03,626 --> 00:24:05,417
GROAN 

310
00:24:05,667 --> 00:24:09,250
No, no, no!
Cancel 'Barteljaap all alone'! 

311
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:11,834
Cancel, cancel! 

312
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:24,334
If you don't say anything,
then eh... I won't say anything either. 

313
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:30,959
Door open! 

314
00:24:36,876 --> 00:24:40,667
Sad Barteljaap, all alone. 

315
00:24:42,751 --> 00:24:45,334
MUSIC: BRIGHT EYES BY ART GARFUNKEL 

316
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:48,709
♪Is it a kind of dream 

317
00:24:48,959 --> 00:24:54,918
♪Floating out on the tide 

318
00:24:55,125 --> 00:25:00,959
♪Following the river of death downstream 

319
00:25:01,167 --> 00:25:05,125
♪Oh, is it a dream? 

320
00:25:05,375 --> 00:25:10,751
♪There's a fog along the horizon...♪